    "name": "Alex Marsh",
    "profile": "Producer, guitarist, songwriter and DJ who released his first record Tonight by Partners In Time in 1993. He continued on to Boy George’s label More Protein where he teamed up with Dave Davis to produce some of Georges work as The Twin and Jesus Loves You. He hit it big in 2006 with the track Something as Silosonic which reached #3 in the UK club charts and spread internationally on labels like Spinnin Records, All Around The World and Vicious. Alex also signed to Ministry Of Sound as one half of Ill Beat Hustlers. Currently he's signed to Sweden's finest - Stoney Boy Music, where is latest release Silosonic \"Words\" hit the UK club chart in June 2014 @ #12.",
